          I wrote the software in Rust and compiled it onto the raspberry pi.
          The software utilizes information from a barometer to estimate the
          rocket's current height. Once it detects an apogee it fires the
          igniters via my custom igniter board. My software stack also
          handles remote ignition and data monitoring, an arming sequence
          built with a finite state machine, and overall data logging.

          Overall, this entire project was a complete exercise in all the
          disciplines of engineering. It required aerodynamic and structural
          design, and simulations. 3D modeling and printing. PCB creation.
          And Software engineering.
